title: PPPP’s Ali Hassan wins PS- 76 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP), Ali Hassan has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-76, Thatha -II , by securing 71,408 votes.
According to unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Altaf Hussain Khichi ,Tehreek-e-Labbaik Pakistan (TLP) who bagged 4,812 vote.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 35.52 %.
